opicID=1815.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Summoned pet weapons with +damage</span><hr size=1> Anyone figured out why the summoned pet only weapons have the +damage on them? Such as the Blade of Walnan having a +3 magic dmg modifier on it. Its not like it increases the damage they do per hit or anything. Anyone have any ideas on this or did Verant just toss it on there to make the stats look better.<br>
<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=465781">Master Nucci</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=salashpenumbra>Salash Penumbra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 410<br> <font color=#333333>(2/4/03 4:01:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1815.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Summoned pet weapons with +damage</span><hr size=1> It's possible it shifts the damage curve up slightly for mobs that are vulnerable to that type of resist, but still maintains the capped damage level. The difference would be hard to measure though as it's so small. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=38898">Salash Penumbra</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> - <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower">Summoner</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> of <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.midnightfury.org">Armies</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->!</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zeem@themagicianstower>Zeem</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 541<br> <font color=#333333>(2/5/03 3:03:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1815.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Or...</span><hr size=1> It is probaly designed by the same person that put Sta, Dex and Str on our belt/girlde and on our pet buffs.<br>
<br>
Stat modifiers aint working on a pet ( you can easy test that by putting a big sta buff on a L4 pet, it wont get a single extra HP. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rhasinfirestorm@themagicianstower>Rhasin Firestorm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1292<br> <font color=#333333>(2/18/03 5:00:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1815.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Or...</span><hr size=1> I don't know how well sta buffs work on lowbie pets (considering hps gained is a measure of class and stat and the mark it's at), but considering BO5 has an attack buff, that seems to work. Burnout also has a Str buff, and that seems to work too (pet hits max more often with burnout than without, shifted damage curve upwards). Belt/Girdle also have +hp on it (a stat buff of sorts), and that's easily provable as working as it bugs low level pets that dip into that 'dead yet got hps from mah belt' flaw.<br>
<br>
It's been said previously that the fire/cold/magic damage on the various blades/fist is for one thing. To let you have a visible reminder what resist that weapon works against, in case you were not lore savy to know who Ixblat, Walnan, or the Kedge were. Pets do not take the damage or delay of the weapons they use. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://&quot;http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=52886&quot;"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.ninjacorp.com/Rhasin_sig.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ylaine76>Ylaine76</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1235<br> <font color=#333333>(2/18/03 5:40:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1815.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Or...</span><hr size=1> Yeah stamina and noticably charisma do not work on pets, my guess is NPCs simply dont have these stats since they dont need them<br>
<br>
However pets do benefit from Dex, agility and strength (well agi is debatable but I dont see why not)<br>
<br>
Wisdom and intelligence its possible but I dont see much point<br>
<br>
Charisma is easy to test for me since Divine Intervention which is based on CHA *never* works on my pet, then again it never works on me either with 190 cha <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
Only reason I have to why stamina doesnt work is because HP gain through stamina is based on your class and NPCs have no player class, yeah they can be called warriors but they really arent.. So they're just given static HP and never gain 0 hp per stamina point, sorta dissapointing<br>
<br>
